[32m│[0m - No different error messages between padding errors vs decryption errors    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The application returns a **generic 400 error for ANY captcha validation   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m failure**, whether due to:                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - Invalid ciphertext (modified cookie)                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - Wrong captcha text                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - Padding errors                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Conclusion: NO PADDING ORACLE VULNERABILITY DETECTED**                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application does NOT exhibit padding oracle behavior because:            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **No distinguishable errors**: Modified ciphertext and wrong captcha text [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m produce identical errors                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **No timing differences**: Response times are consistent regardless of    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m padding validity                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Proper error handling**: The server returns the same generic error for  [32m│[0m
